                            <h1>My Bullfight Experience</h1>
                                <p>I would like to finish with my own experience of a bullfight.  When I went with CEA, I had very little prior knowledge of what would actually happen in the fight.  I was surprised at how ritualized and planned out it was.  I had thought there would be more of a fight between man and bull, a one on one battle.  Clearly, after seeing the bull in action, a single man versus a bull would be over very quickly, resulting in the carting away of the man, not the bull.  But there were planned stages and roles in the event which I knew nothing about, and I was more entertained by the action than the apparent art of it all.  And while I am glad that I was able to experience this important piece of Sapnish culture, I would have to categorize myself in the “not opposed but not interested” group.</p>
